summary:
RIP, Kabosu. - A gentle soul who brought so much happiness into the world. Born on November 2, 2005, Kabosu was rescued from a puppy mill that was shutting down. She was one of 19 Shiba Inus abandoned at that time and was fortunate to be adopted by Atsuko Sato, a Japanese kindergarten teacher, in 2008. Atsuko named her Kabosu after the round, citrus fruit, reflecting the dog's round face.

 Tokenomics - We Love Doge ($WLD) is a Memorial Coin crafted in loving memory of Kabosu, In memory of Kabosu, let us continue to support causes that were dear to her and Atsuko's hearts.
